{{notability|date=September 2018}}
[[File:Iñaki Urlezaga JPG.jpg|thumb|right|Iñaki Urlezaga]]
'''Iñaki Urlezaga''' is an Argentine ballet dancer.

Born in [[La Plata]], Argentina, he trained in his native city and at the "Instituto Superior de Arte of the [[Columbus Theatre]] of [[Buenos Aires]]".{{fact|date=September 2018}} He was apprenticed at the [[New York City Ballet]] and was refined with Laura Alonso.{{fact|date=September 2018}}

He joined the ballet [[Teatro Argentino de La Plata]] led by '''Esmeralda Agoglia''' and in 1993 un the Columbus Ballet where he was the first figure.{{fact|date=September 2018}} He has danced in Europe, South America, Central America and the US.{{fact|date=September 2018}}

In 1995 he joined the [[Royal Ballet]] of [[London]] <ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2001/jul/29/features.review87/a-swan-song-that-fell-flat-on-its-face/ A swan song that fell flat on its face]</ref> where he danced until 2005.{{fact|date=September 2018}}
He is a principal guest dancer with the National Ballet of Netherlands.{{fact|date=September 2018}}

He formed his own company, ''Ballet Concierto'', and serves as a choreographer.{{fact|date=September 2018}} He has choreographed [[Verdi]]'s [[La traviata]] in Spain 2010.{{fact|date=September 2018}} 
