{{Infobox VG | title = Thor: Son of Asgard | image = File:Thor Son of Asgard App.jpg | caption = | developer = [[Disney Mobile Games Studios]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Disney Mobile, Prague Studio|url=http://developedinczech.com/?page=dev&COID=11|website=Devlopedinczech|accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nikola Bornová|url=https://cz.linkedin.com/in/nikolabornova|website=LinkedIn|accessdate=24 July 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140222221453/http://cz.linkedin.com/in/nikolabornova|archivedate=22 February 2014|df=}}</ref> | publisher = [[Marvel Entertainment]] | writer = Bryan J.L. Glass<ref name=Comicsalliance>{{cite web|last1=Goellner |first1=Caleb |title=New ‘Thor: Son of Asgard’ Game Thunders onto iOS Devices [Video] Read More: New ‘Thor: Son of Asgard’ Game Thunders onto iOS Devices [Video] |url=http://comicsalliance.com/new-thor-son-of-asgard-videogame-ios-devices/ |website=Comics Alliance |accessdate=25 August 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140720190803/http://comicsalliance.com/new-thor-son-of-asgard-videogame-ios-devices/ |archivedate=20 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> | released = 10 May 2011 | genre = [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]] | modes = | platforms = [[iOS]] }}
'''''Thor: Son of Asgard''''' is an [[Action-adventure game|action-adventure]] video game developed by Disney Mobile's Prague studio for [[iOS]], based on [[Marvel Comics]]' [[Thor (Marvel Comics)|Thor]].<ref name=GiantB>{{cite web|title=Thor: Son of Asgard|url=http://www.giantbomb.com/thor-son-of-asgard/3030-37677/|website=Giant Bomb|accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>
The story is based on a comics version of Thor. Cutscenes are made from comic book-styled animation. The character itself is on the other hand based on his [[Thor (film)|movie version]], his persona and the suit.<ref name=Tech>{{cite web|last1=Rana|first1=Shayne|title=Thor: Son of Asgard Review|url=http://tech.firstpost.com/reviews/thor-son-of-asgard-review-46362.html|website=Tech2|accessdate=25 August 2014}}</ref>
==Gameplay== Player controls the character of Thor. The game features a simple [[Beat 'em up]] gameplay. Player fights hordes of enemies. His weapon is his [[Mjolnir (comics)|Hammer]] that can be used to hit enemies or block their attack. He can also use some combos including a one hitting all enemies nearby by bolts of lightning.<ref name=stP>{{cite web|last1=Reed|first1=Chris|title=Thor: Son of Asgard Review|url=http://www.slidetoplay.com/review/thor-son-of-asgard-review/|website=slide to Play|accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref><ref name=spy>{{cite web|last1=Nesvadba|first1=Andrew|title=THOR: Son of Asgard Review|url=http://www.appspy.com/review/4896/thor-son-of-asgard-review|website=AppSpy|accessdate=25 August 2014}}</ref>
==Plot== The game follows Thor as he seeks to find out why his sister [[Sif (comics)|Sif]] has apparently betrayed Asgard and joined its enemies. His tasks leads him to variety of worlds including for example Jotuheim and Alfeim. He has to face enemies including Dark Elves, Trolls or Frost Giants.
==Reception== The game has received mixed to negative reviews. It was praised for its graphics but criticised for its gameplay. It was also praised for its vocal work and further look to the universe of Thor.<ref>{{cite web|title=Thor: Son of Asgard|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/thor-son-of-asgard|website=Metacritic|accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>
The most of reviews criticised the game for being repetitive. This objection is linked to a lack of upgrades that some reviewers noted. Controls were also criticised for being frustrating and combat system lacking of depth, being only about button mashing. The animation was also criticised by some critics for being poor.<ref name=Tech/><ref name=appleNapps>{{cite web|last1=Sheridan|first1=Trevor|title=Thor: Son of Asgard|url=http://applenapps.com/review/thor-son-of-asgard#.U_uCyvl_tqU|website=Apple N Apps|accessdate=25 August 2014}}</ref>
